description:
Did you ever dream being the Empress of an Empire on which the sun never sets and who rules the seas; 
or to get the rightful place in the sun for your nation, spreading your Kultur and influence, challenging Britania&rsquo;s mastery of the oceans and deterring jealous rivals with an army nobody can match alone; 
or to free your Slavic brethens from oppression, getting access to the warm seas and dominating Asia; 
or to fulfill your &lsquo;Mission Civilisatrice&rsquo; and perhaps even recover your lost provinces? 

This game is for you!

An historical boardgame for 4 players

Card driven, with events and card points, you take the head of one of the most formidable powers of the era, from 1898 to a possible Great War. 
You will garner victory, prestige, strength and influence by making alliances, destroying adverse ones, controlling up to 11 other secondary powers, placing troops and colonies to expand your empire and hinder rival ones, fomenting strikes and colonial uprisings, leading the naval and armament races, all this under the threat of a looming world war. 
Fashoda, US-Spanish war, Russo-Japanese war, the Boers, the Great Game, German Naval league and Sarajevo are now all yours to confront and overcome&hellip;

&mdash;description from the publisher

In the realm of the Grim Reapers, it is the Joker&rsquo;s party who rules, for now. They oppress the reapers and banish the heretics. The banished Grim Reapers wish nothing but regaining their power, so they assemble secretly, endeavoring to take back their control over the Reaper&rsquo;s Realm through a mysterious sacrificial ritual. However, the assembly room is already penetrated by the Jokers --- the orders of the offerings are disrupted, and the real class of the offerings can&rsquo;t be identified! The clock is ticking, and the right moment for the ritual is about to pass. The Exilers have no choice but to start a &ldquo;Life-and-Death&rdquo; battle with the Jokers&hellip;&hellip;

"Vitamors Conspiro" is a social deduction game of hidden loyalty. Players take the role of either the &ldquo;Exiler&rdquo; or the &ldquo;Joker&rdquo;, through &ldquo;Offering Up a Sacrifice&rdquo; and &ldquo;Start the Ritual&rdquo; to attain victory. Players may start the ritual whenever the number of the character cards on the altar meets the requirements; however, to start the ritual successfully, the combination of the character cards have to be correct, too. That means players may also win the game by cheating their opponents, misleading them to start the ritual with a wrong combination and cause the ritual to fail. When there are 9 character cards on the altar, yet the ritual hasn&rsquo;t been started, the Jokers automatically win the game (they are already in charge of the Reaper&rsquo;s Realm, after all).

